%sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS weblogSessions_timestamps(client_ip STRING, request STRING, timestamp TIMESTAMP, previous_timestamp TIMESTAMP)

%sql
--drop table weblogSessions_timestamps

INSERT INTO weblogSessions_timestamps
    SELECT client, request, timestamp,
        LAG(timestamp) OVER (PARTITION BY client ORDER BY timestamp) AS previous_timestamp
      FROM weblogdata
weblogSessions_timestamps.show()

%sql

CREATE TABLE weblogSessions_sessions
    SELECT *,( unix_timestamp(timestamp) - unix_timestamp(previous_timestamp)) as time_diff,
        CASE WHEN unix_timestamp(timestamp) - unix_timestamp(previous_timestamp) > (60 * 15) -- using 15mins as session interval
             OR previous_timestamp IS NULL
        THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_new_session
    FROM weblogSessions_timestamps
val weblogSessions_ByIds = sqlContext.sql( "SELECT *, SUM(is_new_session) OVER (PARTITION BY client_ip ORDER BY timestamp) AS session_id FROM weblogSessions_sessions")

Determine unique URL visits per session.
To clarify, count a hit to a unique URL only once per session.

paragraphs.text:
val unique_visits = sqlContext.sql("SELECT client_ip, session_id, COUNT(url) AS unique_visits, COUNT(url) / MAX(session_id) AS unique_visits_per_session FROM ( SELECT DISTINCT client_ip, session_id, url FROM weblogSessions_ByIds ) sessions GROUP BY client_ip,session_id order by client_ip,session_id")

unique_visits.coalesce(1).write.csv("s3://sessionize-weblogs/unique_visits")
